Implement a FAQ/Troubleshooting page for bolt.diy. The page should be able to build static html and deployed on github pages later.
Features
- Language toggle right side with globe icon (english/german)
- Toggle dark/light mode bottom right (default dark)
- Troubleshoot/FAQ items are shown as accordion
Generals Requirements
Modern, clean, accessible, responsive styling, state of the art
Use SVGs instead of pngs, jpgs for images
for icons use a library of your choice, dont use svgs for it
Nice/modern animations/effects
colorschema magenta/dark/white
ensure all features are working and shown in the preview
ensure the webapp has base path with a proper name, cause we deploy it into a specific folder on git pages, instead of into the root

Implement a second page for providing command snippets like test curls to verify provider apis are working, 
implement a button to copy these snippets directly
do a proper navigation in the header with a language toggle as well
the FAQ stays the homepage. link the logo also to it.
